      <p>Here, each character has moved from their original position, reflecting their evolution and character arcs. The first important change is that of Lucius and Olivero — note they have only moved along one axis each but have both arrived at the 'truth' for that axis. It's important that Lucius and Olivero do not travel on the same axis, as that would create conflict between their arcs. Having the movements of the positively changed characters be on separate axes allows the themes to better play off one another and gives each character their own space to shine.</p>
