      <p>There may be no more obvious example of a double-edged sword in history than that of modern digital technology. International face time or access to limitless free information on one hand. On the other hand, there is phone addiction, social isolation, environmental impacts, and lack of privacy. The education sector is far from being unaffected, especially with children often less equipped to handle the difficulties of technology.</p>

